rComments: She was the second professor for BIO130. She's a pretty good lecturer as she has a clear voice and is willing to go the extra mile to help students during tutorials. For example, I was sitting really far away from her and she had actually walked all the way from the stage to me. (I felt bad afterwards). However, her exam is harder than the midterm.

Professor Mitchell taught the second-half of BIO130, and the lectures cover all the material that is required for the final exam. She presents the course content in a faster manner than the first-half of the course, but it was still organized. There were a lot of textbook readings, but most of it went into greater detail than was required.

Good lecturer. Includes biology lab techniques and experiment videos in her lectures. Very knowledgable about the subject though lectures can be a little dry. Would take her lectures over reading the textbook any day. Final exam was fair.

Proff. Mitchel is a good professor. Her lectures are at a good pace and well put together. You can tell she puts effort in everything she does. I never had her test yet. Yes, she reads off her slides but this does not mean she doesnt know what she is talking about. Ask her a question and you will tell that she is an expert.

Very dry, uninspiring lectures. She essentially reads off her notes for an hour (I don't think she looked at her audience even once throughout the term). Her exam is reasonable as long as you study the readings thoroughly and read the questions carefully.
